35#ifndef HEIMDAL_KRB5_DB_PLUGIN_H
36#define HEIMDAL_KRB5_DB_PLUGIN_H 1
37
38#define KRB5_PLUGIN_DB "krb5_db_plug"
39#define KRB5_PLUGIN_DB_VERSION_0 0
40
41/** @struct krb5plugin_db_ftable_desc
42 *
43 * @brief Description of the krb5 DB plugin facility.
44 *
45 * The krb5_aname_to_lname(3) function's DB rule is pluggable. The
46 * plugin is named KRB5_PLUGIN_DB ("krb5_db_plug"), with a single minor
47 * version, KRB5_PLUGIN_DB_VERSION_0 (0).
48 *
49 * The plugin consists of a data symbol referencing a structure of type
50 * krb5plugin_db_ftable_desc, with three fields:
51 *
52 * @param init Plugin initialization function (see krb5-plugin(7))
53 *
54 * @param minor_version The plugin minor version number (0)
55 *
56 * @param fini Plugin finalization function
57 *
58 * The init entry point is expected to call heim_db_register(). The
59 * fini entry point is expected to do nothing.
60 *
61 * @ingroup krb5_support
62 */
63typedef struct krb5plugin_db_ftable_desc {
64 int minor_version;
65 krb5_error_code (KRB5_LIB_CALL *init)(krb5_context, void **);
66 void (KRB5_LIB_CALL *fini)(void *);
67} krb5plugin_db_ftable;
68
69#endif /* HEIMDAL_KRB5_DB_PLUGIN_H */
